By Cui Huiying, southern weekly reporter

Southern weekend intern, Yang Xidi, Zhang Yujuan

Editor in chief | Wang Tao

On the one hand is the national and even global caring people's donations, on the other hand is crying out for the shortage of hospital materials, donated to the hospital materials why not enough?

For three consecutive days, due to the prevention and control of new pneumonia material deployment is not timely problem, Wuhan Red Cross frequent boarding hot search.

At 12:00 noon on January 31,2020, Kyushu Tong Medicine Logistics Company (hereinafter referred to as Jiuzhoutong) officially assisted Wuhan Red Cross Society in repacking materials. In Phoenix Satellite TV report, a staff member at Kyushu Tong said emergency medical supplies could be delivered within two hours.

On the afternoon of February 2, Liu Zhifeng, director and head of the secretariat of Kyushu Tong, told southern weekend that the faster one-way donation had reached this speed, "it will be speedier if it is straightened out later" .

Earlier, on January 26, the Ministry of Civil Affairs designated the Hubei Red Cross Society, the Hubei Provincial Charity Federation, the Hubei Youth Development Foundation, the Wuhan Charity Federation and the Wuhan Red Cross Society as the leading five, to receive donations from charitable organizations for the prevention and control of the epidemic in Wuhan, Hubei Province.

After the Wuhan Red Cross Society became embroiled in controversy, as a listed company in the commercial distribution and distribution of medicines, Kyushu Tong mainly assisted in "tallying the goods" and improving the efficiency of material distribution, "We are not responsible for the distribution and delivery of materials, but only responsible for the logistics management of materials in and out of storage, sorting and stacking, " Liu Zhifeng said, adding that the following steps for distribution and delivery are not within the scope of Kyushu's work, "deployment to listen to the Wuhan new pneumonia prevention and Control Headquarters (hereinafter referred to as the headquarters) instructions. "

The headquarters was established on January 20 to lead and direct the epidemic prevention and control work of the whole city of Wuhan. Wuhan Mayor Zhou Xianwang as commander, the headquarters under the emergency support, publicity, transportation, markets, medical treatment, epidemic prevention and control, community, integrated and other 8 working groups.

1
With donation list, delivery is faster

1

###With donation list, delivery is faster

Materials from all over poured into the large exhibition hall of the Hanyang National Museum Center in Wuhan. At one time, this was the warehouse shared by the Red Cross Society of Hubei Province and the Red Cross Society of Wuhan, and supplies from Huanggang and elsewhere.

On February 1 alone, 12,222 items went into the exhibition hall of Hanyang's Guobo Center, Liu Zhifeng said. On the morning of February 3, a warehouse worker told southern weekend that materials donated to the Wuhan Red Cross Society will continue to be shipped to the Hanyang Expo Center in Wuhan, while materials donated to the Hubei Red Cross Society, partial shipment to other warehouses.

According to Phoenix satellite TV earlier reports, the site personnel, a large number of emergency supplies off the plane to find a place can be distributed, do not have to be transported to the warehouse.

At present, not only Kyushu Tong company, but also other companies and government departments have their own responsibilities: Wuhan City to unload goods; Personnel from the Wuhan Market Supervision Administration Bureau are responsible for identifying the quality of goods and whether they are for medical use; personnel from the Wuhan Bureau of Statistics are responsible for counting the quantity of goods and materials.

Waiting at home for delivery, you know exactly what you bought, and the store will also attach a shipping list. But there's a lot of stuff coming in from all over the country. "You don't know what's in it until you open it; you don't know what's in it until you open it; you don't know what's in it until you open it; you don't know what's in it until you open it; you don't know what's in it until you open it; you don't know what's in it until you open it; you don't know what's in it until you open it; you don't know what's in it until you open it; you don't know what's in it until you open it; you don't know what's in it until you open it until you open it.

These difficulties have been encountered by the Red Cross Society before. "although it is clearly stated what materials are to be received, even Sanitary Napkins are included in the materials received, " a staff member of the Red Cross Society of Wuhan told Southern Weekend.

Since Kyushu took over, it has improved the efficiency of material classification and the flow of materials out and in. However, each donation still needs to be registered and documented, and it is more helpful to expedite subsequent disposal if the donor attaches a shipping list.

Masks, protective clothing, goggles and other medical supplies have been placed in the emergency products section, according to our live video report from the Hsinking newspaper.

After the tallying is completed, all goods out of the warehouse have to have a warehouse list. How the goods are delivered depends on whether the goods are donated in a targeted way. "The destination of the targeted donations is more clear, and the delivery will be faster, " Liu Zhifeng said. For example, an export list showed that targeted donations were being sent to Huanggang, Huangshi and other places around Wuhan.

However, while targeted donations will improve the efficiency of distribution, some interviewees were worried that everyone would be targeted to donate to some third-class hospitals, while other hospitals, which also lack supplies, would not receive supplies, there is still a need for some non-directed material for uniform deployment.

If the donor does not specify to whom, the instructions for how much material to allocate to each unit come from the headquarters.

How does command know which hospitals are low on supplies? On February 1, according to a report in Chinese philanthropist, if hospitals are short of supplies, they can report the situation to the provincial health commission or the Wuhan Epidemic Command, which will then issue an order to the city's Red Cross Society according to the inventory situation. Upon receipt of the release order, the Red Cross staff will release the materials to the outside.

According to southern weekend reporters understand that at present, Kyushu Tong is still following this delivery process. After the classification, Kyushu Tong will be drugs, equipment, key equipment product data to the city Health Commission for distribution, non-drug city development and Reform Commission for distribution. After receiving the transfer order from the above-mentioned unit, open the warehouse receipt and print out the Warehouse Picking List in the cloud warehouse system of Kyushu. After the on-site sorting is completed, the stock is checked and confirmed, and the selected materials are put into the temporary storage area according to the distribution unit, waiting for distribution.

Once out of the warehouse, who delivers it and how it is delivered to the units, "whether it's self-pickup or home delivery, I'm not sure, " Liu Zhifeng said. "As far as I know, China Post is a delivery unit. "

Kyushu Tong has 35 staff stationed in the warehouse to work, every night shift staff will be at 24 o'clock in the rolling account, the day of the goods received and delivered to complete a dynamic inventory, to ensure the accuracy of materials.

2
Wuhan Red Cross Society Main Work: answers the consultation telephone, informs the donation procedure

2

###Wuhan Red Cross Society Main Work: answers the consultation telephone, informs the donation procedure

On the evening of February 2,2020, Wang Chao, the head of the propaganda group of the Wuhan Red Cross Society, who was deeply involved in the vortex of public opinion, gave an interview to a reporter from southern weekend. He was aggrieved, even choked up at one point, and was especially pleased to note the news that some companies had helicopter delivered supplies directly to the Wuhan Union Hospital.

"Our hometown and family are in Wuhan. Who wouldn't want to send the most urgently needed supplies to the medical staff in the face of such a severe epidemic? You say we are not able to match, that is indeed objective, but scold us to hoard supplies not to send, it is chilling."

Wang Chao reiterated that until now, the main work of the Wuhan Red Cross has remained the same -- as if to take calls from people all over the country, telling them how to proceed with the donation.

According to a report by Beiqingshen once on February 2, the work of Red Cross volunteers in Wuhan mainly consists of telephone answering, material handling and warehouse management. The largest group is the telephone answering group, which has about 100 people, 30,40 men in warehouse management and materials handling.

"All the reports are about the Red Cross warehouse, but the warehouse belongs to the Wuhan Emergency Response Office and is used by the headquarters, including the circulation, distribution and storage of materials, including the security guards inside, which have nothing to do with the Red Cross and is not under our management, " Wang Chao said.

Some medical staff speculated that the warehouse in line with medical standards of N95 mask backlog, is to be left for the upcoming use of the Vulcan Mountain Hospital, differential treatment caused dissatisfaction.

Wang Chao said he was not aware of the situation and had not heard of the N95 mask being reserved for future use.

Zhan, who is in charge of on-site donation at Huoshenshan Hospital, told the Beijing News on Feb. 1 that they will receive donated materials directly, without going through the Wuhan Red Cross, which is a "special task. " If the donations received by the designated donors can be used, they will report to the Red Cross by making up the procedures.

On February 1, the Red Cross Society of China went to Wuhan to guide and urge the Red Cross societies of Hubei Province and Wuhan to do a good job in the management of the receipt and use of donations, and to ensure that they are standardized, efficient, open and transparent, and take the initiative to accept social supervision, to provide strong support to frontline medical staff.

On the same day, the Wuhan Red Cross made an adjustment to the targeted donation process: If there is a targeted donation of hospitals by units or individuals both at home and abroad, they can directly link up with the targeted donation medical institutions, and after confirmation, they can send the materials directly to the recipient units.

On January 30, Wuhan Union Hospital asked for Medical Supplies "not urgent! There is no more! " On Weibo and the social network. That afternoon, the People's Daily's official microblog reposted a message that quickly drew attention. Subsequently, Hubei Province Integrated Chinese and Western Medicine Hospital, Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital, and many other first-line hospitals to prevent and control the epidemic have issued material emergency announcement.

At least 290,000 surgical masks, 930 protective suits, 147,500 pairs of gloves and 4,500 isolation suits arrived at the Wuhan Union Hospital in just two days from Jan. 31 to Feb. 1, according to southern weekend reporters.

Another batch of 2 tons of medical protective equipment donated by caring people arrived in the early morning of February 1. A logistics support staff of the hospital said in an interview that they needed 700-800 sets of protective clothing every day, the supplies will last about a week.

However, in view of the current epidemic situation, front-line medical workers may face the prevention and control work lasting several months, and still need more support from all sectors of society.

At a news conference held by the State Council Information Office on Feb. 3, Deputy Director of the National Development and Reform Commission, Lian Weiliang, said that Ministry of Transport of the People's Republic of China has used five existing logistics parks to set up a road transport service station for emergency supplies into Hubei, "No stopping, no inspection, no charge" for the transportation of medical materials and other related vehicles will be given priority. He also said that mask companies can run full steam production, after the epidemic surplus production, as long as the standard government will be collected and stored.

On This Day, many enterprises have started work. "Many production enterprises have been taken over by the government, and productivity will be restored as the Spring Festival holiday ends, " An entrepreneur who ordered masks for his employees was told by southern weekend that orders from several production enterprises had been "run off" .
